{"lemma":"ثَرَى","slug":"ثَرَى","root":"ث.ر.#","root_slug":"ث-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ثَرَى","root":"ثري","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4406","n4417","n4413","n4415"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ثَرِيَ (ṯariya) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"earth, soil"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dew"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/θa.ran/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4406","headword_ar":"ثَرِىٌّ","root":"vrw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"numerous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[applied to a company of men;] and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variy~apN","text_ar":"ثَرِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to spears ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rimaAHN","text_ar":"رِمَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (TA:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"cattle, or other property; (S, M, K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varK","text_ar":"ثَرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much, cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avoraY","text_ar":"اَثْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvorK","text_ar":"مُثْرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) so too ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varowaAnu","text_ar":"ثَرْوَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounding"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and [its fem.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varowaY","text_ar":"ثَرْوَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman, (T, S, M, K,) likewise signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much, cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K:) the dim. of this last is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuray~aA","text_ar":"ثُرَيَّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, S, M, K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varK","text_ar":"ثَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  And see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrY","text_ar":"ثرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","T","M","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n4417","headword_ar":"ثَرِىٌّ","root":"vrY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variy~apN","text_ar":"ثَرِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varK","text_ar":"ثَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:       -A2-  and see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrw","text_ar":"ثرو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4413","headword_ar":"ثرّى","root":"vrY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavoriyapN","text_ar":"تَثْرِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He moistened"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) a place, (T,) or earth, or the ground, or dust, (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawiyq","text_ar":"سَوِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or meal of parched barley or wheat], (S, TA,) and any other thing: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sprinkled"},{"kind":"text","text":"a place: (S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he poured water upon, and then stirred about, and mixed up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the preparation of milk termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqiT","text_ar":"اَقِط"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawiyq","text_ar":"سَوِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his hands to cleave to the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two prostrations in prayer, not separating them therefrom until he performed the second prostration."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n4415","headword_ar":"ثَرًى","root":"vrY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Moisture; humidity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) of the earth: (S, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAb","text_ar":"تُرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is not moist is not called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varFY","text_ar":"ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as, when moistened, does not become cohesive mud"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varoyaA='u","text_ar":"ثَرْيَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an epithet used as a subst.]: (AO, T, * K, TA: [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varayA'","text_ar":"ثَرَياء"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA taHota Alv~aray","text_ar":"مَا تَحْتَ الثَّرَي"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xx. 5], being explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is beneath the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~araY","text_ar":"الثَّرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and *"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avoraY","text_ar":"اَثْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, being thus used as a proper name, is imperfectly decl.: (Ham p. 351:) dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varayaAni","text_ar":"ثَرَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varawaAni","text_ar":"ثَرَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, M, K: [but the sing. of the latter should be written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varFA","text_ar":"ثَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avoraA=o","text_ar":"اَثْرَا=ْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AilotaqaY Alv~arayaAni","text_ar":"اِلْتَقَى الثَّرَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two moistures met,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have met,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said when the rain has sunk into the ground so that it has met the moisture of the earth. (S, M, K.) Accord. to IAar, it was also said by a man, (M,) or by an Arab of the desert, (K,) who, (M, K,) being naked, (K,) clad himself with a fur-garment, (M, K,) without a shirt; (M;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hair of the pubes and the soft hair of the fur-garment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahorN varaY wa$ahorN taraY wa$ahorN maroEaY wa$ahorN A@sotawaY","text_ar":"شَهْرٌ ثَرَى وَشَهْرٌ تَرَى وَشَهْرٌ مَرْعَى وَشَهْرٌ ا@سْتَوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A month"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of moisture"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the rain begins, and sinks into the ground, and moistens and softens the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahorN *uw varFY","text_ar":"شَهْرٌ ذُو ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a month in which thou seest the heads of the herbage grown forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahorN taraY fiyhi ruw^uwsa Aln~abaAti","text_ar":"شَهْرٌ تَرَى فِيهِ رُوُوسَ النَّبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a month in which the herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall enough to be pastured upon by the cattle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, * M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a month in which it is full-grown and erect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, M.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaA varaY AlmaA='i mina Alfarasi","text_ar":"بَدَا ثَرَى المَا=ءِ مِنَ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sweat of the horse appeared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY laA^aray varaY AlgaDabi fiY wajohi fulaAnK","text_ar":"اـِنِّى لَاَرَي ثَرَى الغَضَبِ فِى وَجْهِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I see the effect of anger in the face of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwaA@bonu varaAhaA","text_ar":"هُوَا@بْنُ ثَرَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the knowing with respect to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Hence, as being likened to moist earth,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good; anything good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (M, K. [For"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayor","text_ar":"خَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", Golius appears to have found, in a copy of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hayoz","text_ar":"حَيْز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this, which he has rendered “Terræ tractus,” he has given as a signification, not of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varFY","text_ar":"ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", but of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varaA='N","text_ar":"ثَرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varFY","text_ar":"ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", he also explains as meaning “ terra. ” ]) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN qariybu Alv~araY","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ قَرِيبُ الثَّرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is a person from whom good is easy of attainment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it may mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person from whom good seems to be easy of attainment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in either case likened to land of which the moist earth is near the surface: that the phrase may have the latter meaning appears from what here follows]. (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a fulaAnFA laqariybu Alv~ariY baEiydu Aln~abaTi","text_ar":"اـِنَّ فُلَانًا لَقَرِيبُ الثَّرِى بَعِيدُ النَّبَطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily such a one is a person who promises but who does not fulfil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh and vigorous friendship."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yabobasi Alv~araY bayoniY wabayonahu","text_ar":"لَمْ يَبْبَسِ الثَّرَى بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fresh and vigorous friendship between me and him has not withered"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: whence the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bayoniY wabayona fulaAnK","text_ar":"مَا بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"*"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvorK","text_ar":"مُثْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That"},{"kind":"text","text":"friendship"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is between me and such a one is fresh and vigorous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e., it has not ceased, or become severed. (S, * M.) Jereer says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falaA tuwbisuwA bayoniY wabayonakumu Alv~araY\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      faA_in~a Al~a*ay bayoniY wabayonakumu muvoriY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And wither not the fresh and vigorous friendship between me and you; for that which is between me and you is fresh and vigorous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","M","K"]}]}}